### Trash API Tests
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api

### Get bearer token (log in first)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "YourPassword123"
}

### Set token from login response
@authToken = {{login.response.body.data.accessToken}}

### Get All Trash Contents (files + folders)
GET {{baseUrl}}/trash/contents
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Empty Trash (permanently delete all trash contents)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/trash/empty
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Soft Delete a File (move to trash)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/files/64a5b7e9c12e456789abcdef
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Permanently Delete a File
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/files/64a5b7e9c12e456789abcdef/permanent
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Restore a File from Trash
POST {{baseUrl}}/files/64a5b7e9c12e456789abcdef/restore
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Get Trashed Files
GET {{baseUrl}}/files/trash/contents
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Soft Delete a Folder (move to trash)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/folders/64a5b7e9c12e456789abcdef
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Permanently Delete a Folder
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/folders/64a5b7e9c12e456789abcdef/permanent
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Restore a Folder from Trash
POST {{baseUrl}}/folders/64a5b7e9c12e456789abcdef/restore
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Get Trashed Folders
GET {{baseUrl}}/folders/trash/contents
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
